meta {
  name: Refresh Token
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
  }
}

script:post-response {
  if (res.body?.data?.accessToken) {
    bru.setEnvVar("accessToken", res.body.data.accessToken);
    bru.setEnvVar("refreshToken", res.body.data.refreshToken);
  }
}

docs {
  ## Refresh Token

  `POST /auth/refresh` — exchanges a valid, unrevoked refresh token for a new access/refresh pair. Refresh tokens rotate on every use (the old one is invalidated). Public (no auth) — the refresh token itself is the credential, sent in the body.

  ### Body
  | Field | Type | Required |
  |---|---|---|
  | `refreshToken` | string | yes (non-empty) |

  ### Response
  `200 OK` — `data`: `{ accessToken, refreshToken, user }` (new pair).

  ### Errors
  `invalidRefreshToken` if expired, forged, or already rotated/revoked.
}